		<div id="comment_body_64232078"><p><div class="quote"><p> Host your own mail.  Host your own web server (for most companies, their web site is a glorified vanity page).  Contract with a local IT company to keep it running if you're too small to have your own staff.  The only thing that should be hosted is your off site backups.</p></div><p>Let's try that again...</p><p>If you're small, you should absolutely not host your own email and web server.  You will have to deal with a deluge of spam.  You'll have to keep up with security of your server on the internet, including monitoring.  To do that, you need an experienced, dedicated staff.  If uptime is important, you'll have to spend on providing redundancy.</p><p>Better to outsource email / web to a provider that has teams dedicated to each item that will likely be better at it than your IT team.  Sign a SLA<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

