	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64231666"><p>I agree,</p><p>Cuts to IT when cloud resources need management and maintenance cause some big blowouts in cloud subscription costs.</p><p>I still see to this day the non-sensical lift and shift being a goal of Enterprise organisations.  Expecting that cloud will solve ever growing costs of maintaining everything.  As application usage, data rate, and data storage increase if your crude infra that you uplifted to the cloud doesn't adapt it's cost are going to spiral.</p><p>You can't treat cloud as simply on-prem virtualisation.</p><p>S<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
